content.headline: Joby, NASA Simulation Demonstrates Up To 120 Air Taxi Operations Per Hour in Busy Airspace
content.summary: SANTA CRUZ, Calif., December 20, 2023--Joby Aviation, Inc. (NYSE:JOBY), a company developing electric vertical take-off and landing (eVTOL) aircraft for commercial passenger service, today announced it has successfully completed a series of air traffic simulations with NASA’s Ames Research Center that evaluated how air taxi operations can be integrated into today’s airspace, including at busy airports, using existing air traffic control (ATC) tools and procedures.
